description:
We are looking for the high calibre candidate to fill the Home Delivery - Sales & Customer Service Officer in our office:


Job Responsibilities


Handling inquires and emails, retrieve voicemails and make follow-up calls to customers;
Handle sales order in Magento / NAV system and arrange delivery date;
Provide administrative support to team not limit to roster and uniform; 
Prepare regular sales reports and analysis;
Ensure customer satisfaction and resolve any customer concerns that may arise in advance; 
Manage stock for Home Delivery and avoid out of stock
Coordinate with internal and external customers, as well as daily delivery coordination in order to meet with KPIs
Handle delivery documentations, filing and reports
Liaise and follow up with customers' order verification / amendment with relevant departments
Maintain accurate records on all orders, inquiries & customer feedback cases
Provide support to sales and marketing on Home Delivery
Handle ad-hoc project as assigned

 Skills Requirement

Diploma or above;
1 year relevant experience in customer service & sales coordination;
Proficient in MS office application ( Excel & Word ) and Chinese/English Word Processing;
Excellent customer service and communication skills
Good command of spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin.
Immediate availability is preferred

We offer attractive remunerations, including year-end double pay, group medical and life insurance, public holiday, etc. Interested parties please apply with full resume, current and expected salary to HR Department.

All personal data collected will be solely used for recruitment-related purposes.

Job Responsibilities

Handle inbound calls for appointment booking and general enquiries;
Maintain good customer relationship;
5.5 days work per week
Morning shift from Mon - Fri: 8:30am - 6:30pm, Sat: 9:00am - 1:00pm
Rest day on Sunday & Public Holiday

Job Requirements

HKDSE/ HKCEE or above;
With good customer services skill;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Ability to work positively in a fast-paced environment

We offer competitive pay and fringe benefits. Interested parties please send your full resume with current salary and expected salary  to Human Resources Department, Quality HealthCare Medical Services Limited, 3/F, Skyline Tower, 39 Wang Kwong Road, Kowloon Bay, Kowloon or by clicking 'Apply Now".

(All applications will be treated in strict confidence and data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only)

Your role

Provide expert knowledge support to Customer Officers
Handle customer enquiries / complaints / disputes and escalate to management when needed;
Provide backend support to smoothen the operation;
Handle escalation cases from Retail and referral cases from head office;
Solve problems proactively and provide timely resolution to ensure minimal impact to the operation;
Actively participating in continuous improvement programs entailing changes to processes and functions;
Deliver a satisfactory service through telephone / email and contribute to achievement of various prescribed service targets;
Carry out any ad hoc duties as requested;

To succeed in this role

F.5 or above;
A minimum of one year experience in contact centre operation would be an advantage;
Demonstrated analytical, problem solving and decision making skills;
Communicate clearly and concisely, both orally and in writing in Cantonese, English and Mandarin;
Intermediate to advanced skills of Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint and Word;
Able to work shift duty, 48 working hours per week;


Working Location: Tuen Mun / Kowloon Bay

Attractive remuneration package with non-sales nature
14 days' paid annual leave
Comprehensive medical coverage
Non-Contributory Provident Fund
Free Shuttle bus

Responsibilities:

Visit customers and reporting to management team in a regular basis;
Promote services to clients and customers, network will be an advantage;
Communicate and reflect customer requirements;
Work with the team to achieve sales targets;
Update customer’s status and market information to management team, etc.
Any other duties as assigned by the Supervisor/ Manager of the Employer or other associated or subsidiary company(ies) of the Employer.

 Qualification

Bachelor’s Degree in Science or Biology related discipline is basic requirement, Master Degree or above preferred
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Sales Representative or Sales Manage
Good interpersonal, presentation and communication skills, and teamwork
Meticulous, well-organized, responsible, and self-motivated.
Proficiency in written and spoken English & Chinese (both Cantonese and Mandarin)

Responsibilities


Understand customers' needs and conduct necessary follow-up to meet sales target;
Guide and help customers make the best choice that suit their needs;
Maintain good relationship with business partners;
Work closely with internal parties to ensure timely, efficient and effective service to customers;
Assist in other ad-hoc assignments as required;

Requirements


Positive thinking, outgoing, independent, aggressive;
Able to work under pressure and independently;
5-day work week on roster is required, including weekends;
Able to standby anytime in responding to customers;
Hands-on experience from retailing would be an advantage;
Good command of Cantonese, Mandarin and English;
Immediately availability would be a definite advantage.

Job Responsibilities

Handle inbound calls from internal and external customers for general enquiries & insurance;
Maintain good customer relationship;
5 days work per week, 9 hours per day.
Shift duty required, roaster duty up to 10pm

Job Requirements

HKDSE/ HKCEE or above;
With good customer services skill;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
With working experience in call centre and claim are preferred;
Ability to work positively in a fast-paced environment.

We offer competitive pay and fringe benefits. Interested parties please send your full resume with current salary and expected salary to Human Resources Department, Quality HealthCare Medical Services Limited, 3/F, Skyline Tower, 39 Wang Kwong Road, Kowloon Bay, Kowloon or by clicking 'Apply Now".

(All applications will be treated in strict confidence and data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only)

Job Responsibilities:

Provide technical support for installation work orders;
Responsible for order management including order dispatching, incomplete order follow up, order status & equipment record updating;
Prepare order status tracking report & Hotline daily record for management analysis;
Co-ordinate with internal team to facilitate smooth & on-time service delivery.



Job Requirements:

Form 5 / HKDES graduate;
Minimum 1-year experience in customer service;
Work experience in Telecommunication Industry is highly preferred;
Able to read & write both English & Chinese;
Computer Literacy;
Shift duty is required.

We offer competitive salary package and career development opportunity. Free company coach is provided.  Interested parties, please quote our reference number and apply with full resume, present and expected salary, by clicking “APPLY NOW”. 

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for consideration of your application for the relevant post within HGC Global Communications Limited. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly according to our Personal Information Collection Statement, a copy of which will be available upon written request. Information of unsuccessful candidates will be destroyed within six months.
